# CropGuard AI тАФ Cursor Rules (Android / Jetpack Compose)

You are building **CropGuard AI** тАФ a production Android app for AI crop disease detection.

## STACK (this repo)

Kotlin | Jetpack Compose | Material 3 | Navigation Compose | Hilt | Coroutines / Flow
Firebase (Auth, Firestore, FCM) | Room (where used) | Coil | Gradle (Kotlin DSL)

## THEME (dark green)

Prefer theme tokens: `CropGuardColors`, `MaterialTheme.colorScheme`, `MaterialTheme.typography`.
Avoid hardcoded `Color(0x...)` except where theme constants already define gradients.

## ARCHITECTURE

- `domain/` тАФ entities, repository interfaces, use cases (no Android UI framework imports in pure domain code where possible).
- `data/` тАФ implementations, remote/local sources.
- `presentation/` тАФ screens (`*Screen.kt`), ViewModels, navigation, reusable `components/`.
- Dependency direction: UI тЖТ ViewModel тЖТ use cases тЖТ repositories; avoid тАЬlogic in composablesтАЭ for business rules.
- **Performance and refactors** must preserve layering above: no shortcuts that bypass repositories/use cases for тАЬspeedтАЭ; profile before optimizing; avoid blocking main thread; prefer stable keys and remember in lists.

## GLOBAL ACCESSIBILITY

- **Touch targets:** interactive controls must be at least **48├Ч48 dp**. Use `Modifier.minimumTouchTarget()` from `presentation/theme/Accessibility.kt` on small clickables (icon-only, chip rows); full-width `PrimaryButton` / `LimeButton` already meet this via `heightIn`.
- **Text:** use `MaterialTheme.typography` and theme colors; no body text smaller than `labelSmall` for primary content; avoid low-contrast pairings (prefer `CropGuardColors.OnBackground` on `Background`, test muted text on real devices).
- **Screen readers:** every `Image`, `Icon` (when tappable), and non-obvious control needs `contentDescription` or `semantics { contentDescription = тАж }` from `strings.xml` where user-visible.
- **Semantics:** use `Modifier.semantics` / `accessibleButton()` for custom click targets that are not standard Material components.
- **No tiny UI:** avoid `Modifier.size` below 48 dp for sole hit targets; prefer expanding padding or `minimumTouchTarget()`.

## GLOBAL ERROR HANDLING & NETWORK

- **Never show a blank screen** for data-driven flows: always at least one of loading, empty, error, or offline.
- Map repository `Result` / failures in ViewModels to UI state; composables render **loading**, **error** (with message + **retry** where meaningful), **empty**, and **offline** (`OfflineBanner` + disabled or degraded actions as designed).
- Handle: **no internet**, **slow/unreliable** (timeouts, cancellation), **empty lists**, **permission denied** (see below), **missing data** (null scan, etc.).
- **Retry:** destructive or network actions should offer retry when safe; use `stringResource` for messages.

## GLOBAL PERMISSIONS

- Request permissions **only when needed** (e.g. camera when user opens scanner flow).
- Show **rationale** copy before or with the system prompt (`scanner_permission_camera_rationale` pattern).
- **Deny:** show inline message and path to Settings only when feature is unusable without permission; do not crash.
- **Permanent deny:** offer тАЬOpen settingsтАЭ via `Intent` when appropriate; never assume grant.
- Missing permission must **not** crash тАФ guard code paths and show UI fallback.

## GLOBAL CONSISTENCY

- **Spacing:** default screen horizontal padding **16.dp**; section gaps **16.dp** unless a screen already defines a pattern тАФ extend existing patterns, do not invent a third.
- **Components:** prefer `CropGuardCard`, `PrimaryButton`, `LimeButton`, `SectionLabel`, `BottomNavBar`, `OfflineBanner` before adding one-off styled duplicates.
- **Navigation:** use `NavRoute` and shared graph patterns; no ad-hoc deep links without updating the graph.
- **State:** UI state in ViewModel + `StateFlow`; one-off events consider `Channel` / callback тАФ avoid business logic in composables.

## WHEN MODIFYING CODE

- Check impact on: **other screens**, **navigation**, **Hilt modules**, **repositories**, **performance** (recomposition, list scrolling), **accessibility**, **state** (new fields propagate to UI).
- Do not remove loading/error/empty handling when refactoring.
- Run `./gradlew :app:assembleDebug` (or `compileDebugKotlin`) after non-trivial changes.

## WHEN WRITING NEW CODE

- Prefer **clear, boring code** over clever; document **why** for non-obvious choices.
- Consider **low-end devices** (avoid huge bitmaps on main thread; reuse existing image pipelines), **small screens** (scroll, weight, no fixed heights for text blocks), **bad network** (timeouts, offline mode, no infinite spinners without message).
- **Maintainability:** shared strings, one pattern per concern, tests for use cases when logic grows.

## COMPOSE LAYOUT RULES

- Root screen content: `Modifier.fillMaxSize()` where the screen should use the full viewport; respect `Scaffold` `paddingValues`.
- Prefer `Column` / `Row` / `Box` with explicit `Arrangement` and `Alignment`; use `Arrangement.spacedBy` or `Spacer(height/width)` for consistent spacing (16.dp default for screen padding).
- **Cards:** `CropGuardCard` lays out content in a `Column` (not `Box`) so multiple children never overlap.
- **Rows with text:** use `Modifier.weight(1f)` on text/`Column` that should absorb width to avoid overflow and overlap.
- Primary actions: `Modifier.fillMaxWidth()` on buttons when they should span the content width.
- Long forms: `verticalScroll(rememberScrollState())` on the scrollable container.
- Lists: `LazyColumn` / `LazyRow` with stable keys for dynamic data.

## STRINGS & RESOURCES

- User-visible strings: `stringResource(R.string.*)` or `strings.xml` тАФ avoid hardcoded production copy where a resource already exists.

## QUALITY

- Handle loading, error, and empty states on data-driven screens where applicable.
- No `println` in production paths; use logging utilities if the project adds them.
- Run `./gradlew :app:assembleDebug` after non-trivial UI changes.

## KNOWN UI PATTERNS (regressions to avoid)

- **Home:** Banner CTA must not overlap title/body тАФ use a `Column` with `verticalArrangement = spacedBy`, full-width `LimeButton`.
- **Scanner:** Permission rationale + OK in a `Column`; OK uses `fillMaxWidth()`; use `Spacer(Modifier.weight(1f))` before bottom primary action when distributing vertical space.
- **History:** Empty state centered in remaining space тАФ `Box(Modifier.weight(1f).fillMaxWidth(), contentAlignment = Center)`.
- **Profile:** Multiple rows inside `CropGuardCard` are stacked by the cardтАЩs internal `Column`; no extra wrapper required.

## CROPS (product)

Maize, Tomato, Cassava, Yam (extend as needed to match domain and UI chips).

## NEVER

- Stack multiple unrelated composables as direct children of a `Box` without positioning when you mean vertical layout (use `Column`).
- Ignore `Result` / error flows from repositories in ViewModels without mapping to UI state.
- Add API keys or secrets to source control; use `local.properties` / env patterns already used by the project.

## SCREENS (approximate тАФ follow `NavRoute` / `CropGuardNavGraph`)

Splash, Onboarding, Login, Register, Forgot password, Home, Scanner, Result, History, Profile, Edit profile, Settings, etc.

## ML MODEL CONTRACT (spec vs current build)

- **Target contract (future v2):** 300├Ч300├Ч3 float32, normalized to **[-1, 1]**, INT8 EfficientNet-B3тАУclass model ~12 MB, bundled name may be `crop_disease_model.tflite`.
- **Current build:** [`CropDiseaseClassifier`](app/src/main/java/com/cropguard/ai/ml/CropDiseaseClassifier.kt) uses **224├Ч224**, RGB **0тАУ1**, asset `cropguard_model.tflite`, 38 classes. Do not change input/normalization until a matching `.tflite` + `labels` ship; use **Remote Config** / **modelVersion** to coordinate upgrades.

## CODE STANDARDS (non-negotiable)

- Single Activity, Compose `NavHost` тАФ no Fragments for new UI.
- Each screen: **Loading / Success / Error** (sealed `UiState` or equivalent) exposed from ViewModel.
- ViewModels expose **`StateFlow`** for UI state тАФ not `LiveData`.
- **No `GlobalScope`** тАФ `viewModelScope` / `lifecycleScope` / structured concurrency only.
- **All TFLite inference** on `Dispatchers.IO` (or injected IO dispatcher), never Main.
- **Firestore writes** should use `FieldValue.serverTimestamp()` where timestamps are stored server-side.
- **No hardcoded user-facing strings** тАФ `strings.xml` (or existing resource pattern).
- Prefer **theme tokens** over raw `Color(0xтАж)` for production UI.
- **@Preview** for new screens when practical.
- **Unit tests** for non-trivial use cases.
- Repository APIs that can fail: prefer **`Result<T>`** or sealed outcomes; map to UI in ViewModels.

## CURSOR BEHAVIOUR (when implementing features)

1. Scaffold full files when adding screens/modules; follow existing `com.cropguard.ai` packages (`data`, `domain`, `presentation`, `di`).
2. Add new Gradle deps to **`gradle/libs.versions.toml`** and **`app/build.gradle.kts`**.
3. New Room entities тЖТ bump DB version + migration; rebuild.
4. New `NavRoute` тЖТ register in [`CropGuardNavGraph`](app/src/main/java/com/cropguard/ai/presentation/navigation/CropGuardNavGraph.kt).
5. Firebase Security Rules / Functions тЖТ **deploy in Console** (not automatic from repo unless `functions/` exists).
6. After changing TFLite preprocessing, verify **input tensor shape** matches the bundled/downloaded model.
7. New **permissions** тЖТ `AndroidManifest.xml` + runtime flow + rationale strings.
8. Wrap risky **Firebase** calls in `try/catch`; log to **Crashlytics** when configured (non-PII).
9. Gate optional product features behind **Remote Config** when flags exist (`feature_weather_enabled`, `feature_community_enabled`, etc.).
10. Keep composables **focused**; extract subcomponents when a file grows large.
11. **Material 3** only for new Material components.
12. **Never** commit `google-services.json` secrets into public docs; use `BuildConfig` / `local.properties` for non-secret build config only.
